t%20months%20after%20they%20disappeared%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ENASA%20released%20a%20new%20image%20of%20the%20recently-recovered%20long-lost%20space%20tomatoes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAstronaut%20Frank%20Rubio%20misplaced%20the%20tomatoes%20in%20March%20while%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20fruits%20were%20found%20earlier%20this%20month%20slightly%20discolored%20and%20dehydrated.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EImagine%20what%20would%20happen%20to%20a%20tomato%20if%20you%20lost%20it%20in%20your%20home%20%E2%80%94%20here%20on%20Earth%20%E2%80%94%20and%20found%20it%20eight%20months%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20red%20fleshy%20fruit%20would%20turn%20into%20a%20horrifically%20unrecognizable%20clump%20of%20white%20and%20black%20fuzz%2C%20worn%20down%20by%20time%20and%20bacteria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20in%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20space-grown%20tomatoes%20that%20NASA%20astronaut%20Frank%20Rubio%20mistakenly%20lost%20on%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20earlier%20this%20year%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmissing-space-tomato-found-iss-nasa-astronaut-accused-ate-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturned%20up%20last%20week%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20eight%20months%20after%20they%20went%20missing%2C%20vindicating%20Rubio%2C%20whose%20colleagues%20had%20accused%20him%20of%20eating%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20the%20tomatoes%20look%20remarkably%20good%20%E2%80%94%20dare%20we%20say%2C%20edible%3F%20%E2%80%94%20considering%20the%20ordeal%20they%20went%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fmissions%2Fstation%2Fnasa-lets-ketchup-on-international-space-station-tomato-research%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%20on%20Thursday%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20NASA%20shared%20a%20new%20image%20of%20what%20the%20rogue%20fruits%20looked%20like%20when%20they%20were%20found%