ost-similar-to-hitler%2Farticleshow%2F105999918.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22SC%20Suspends%20Conviction%20of%20BSP%20MP%20Afzal%20Ansari%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20with%20a%202%3A1%20majority%2C%20has%20suspended%20the%20conviction%20of%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20MP%20Afzal%20Ansari%20under%20the%20UP%20Gangster%20Act%2C%20allowing%20the%20restoration%20of%20his%20Lok%20Sabha%20membership.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20he%20can%20attend%20House%20proceedings%2C%20he%20cannot%20cast%20his%20votes%20or%20receive%20perks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court21-majority-suspends-conviction-of-bsp-mp-afsal-ansari-dissenting-judge-says-impact-on-electorate-cant-be-considered-244561%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20further%20clarified%20that%20Ansari%20shall%20not%20be%20disqualified%20to%20contest%20future%20election(s)%20during%20the%20pendency%20of%20his%20criminal%20appeal%20before%20the%20high%20court.%20If%20he%20is%20elected%2C%20such%20an%20election%20will%20be%20subject%20to%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20First%20Criminal%20Appeal%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20asked%20the%20Allahabad%20high%20court%20to%20decide%20his%20criminal%20appeal%20expeditiously%20before%20June%2030%2C%202024%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnsari%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbsp-mp-afzal-ansari-disqualified-lok-sabha%5C%22%3Ewas%20disqualified%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20on%20May%201%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20representing%20the%20Ghazipur%20Parliamentary%20Constituency%20of%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Gangsters%20Act%20case%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbsp-mp-afzal-ansari-disqualified-lok-sabha%5C%22%3Ewas%20registered%3C%2Fa%3E%20against%20the%20Ansari%20brothers%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20murder%20of%20BJP%20MLA%20Krishnanand%20Rai%20in%20November%202005%20and%20the%20kidnapping%20and%20murder%20of%20Vishva%20Hindu%20Parishad%20leader%20Nand%20Kishore%20Rungta%20in%20January%201997.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20majority%20judgment%20said%20that%20staying%20a%20conviction%20should%20occur%20only%20under%20exceptional%20circumstances%2C%20particularly%20when%20allowing%20the%20conviction%20to%20operate%20would%20cause%20irreparable%20damage%20and%20the%20convict%20cannot%20be%20compensated%20later%20if%20acquitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20say%20so%20primarily%20for%20the%20reason%20that%20the%20potential%20ramifications%20of%20declining%20to%20suspend%20such%20a%20conviction%20are%20multifaceted.%20On%20the%20one%20hand%2C%20it%20would%20deprive%20the%20Appellant%E2%80%99s%20constituency%20of%20its%20legitimate%20representation%20in%20the%20Legislature%2C%20since%20a%20bye-election%20may%20not%20be%20held%20given%20the%20remainder%20tenure%20of%20the%20current%20Lok%20Sabha.%20Conversely%2C%20it%20would%20also%20impede%20the%20Appellant%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20represent%20his%20constituency%20based%20on%20the%20allegations%2C%20the%20veracity%20whereof%20is%20to%20be%20scrutinised%20on%20a%20re-appraisal%20of%20the%20entire%20evidence%20in%20the%20First%20Criminal%20Appeal%20pending%20before%20the%20high%20court%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%20the%20court%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20also%20said%20that%20the%20conviction%20will%20prevent%20the%20appellant%20from%20contesting%20elections%20for%20ten%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERegarding%20the%20point%20of%20%E2%80%98moral%20turpitude%E2%80%99%20and%20the%20issue%20of%20criminalisation%20of%20politics%2C%20the%20court%20said%20that%20there%20were%20substantial%20doubts%20cast%20on%20the%20criminal%20antecedents%20of%20the%20petitioner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Court%20added%20that%20it%20has%20to%20go%20strictly%20by%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlthough%20%E2%80%98moral%20turpitude%E2%80%99%20may%20carry%20relevance%20within%20the%20context%20of%20elected%20representatives%2C%20the%20courts%20are%20bound%20to%20construe%20the%20law%20in%20its%20extant%20state%20and%20confine%20their%20deliberations%20to%20those%20facets%20explicitly%20outlined%2C%20rather%20than%20delving%20into%20considerations%20pertaining%20to%20the%20moral%20rectitude%20or%20ethical%20character%20of%20actions.%20This%20is%20especially%20true%20when%20it%20is%20solely%20motivated%20by%20the%20convicted%20individual%E2%80%99s%20status%20as%20a%20political%20representative%2C%20with%20the%20aim%20of%20disqualification%20pursuant%20to%20the%20Representation%20of%20Peoples%20Act%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20dissenting%20judge%2C%20Justice%20Dipankar%20Datta%2C%20said%20that%20no%20preferential%20treatment%20can%20be%20given%20to%20politicians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20fact%20that%20the%20court%20is%20approached%20by%20a%20parliamentarian%2Flegislator%2C%20by%20itself%2C%20should%20not%20be%20viewed%20with%20such%20importance%20and%20indispensability%20that%20his%20status%20should%20tilt%20the%20scales%20in%20his%20favour.%20Would%20it%20be%20fair%20that%20a%20convict%2C%20no%20matter%20how%20mighty%20he%20is%20and%20whatever%20position%20he%20holds%2C%20gets%20a%20preferential%20treatment%20as%20compared%20to%20an%20under-trial%3F%20Should%20the%20courts%20go%20out%20of%20the%20way%20to%20stay%20the%20conviction%20or%20suspend%20execution%20of%20the%20order%20under%20appeal%20when%20no%20Fundamental%20or%20other%20Constitutional%20right%20of%20the%20convict%20would%20be%20abrogated%20if%20a%20stay%20were%20not%20granted%3F%20To%20our%20mind%2C%20the%20answers%2C%20as%20traced%20through%20the%20aforesaid%20legal%20and%20constitutional%20framework%2C%20would%20unerringly%20be%20in%20the%20negative.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJustice%20Datta%20advocated%20a%20higher%20stand%20to%20be%20applied%20against%20a%20Parliamentarian%20as%20allowing%20a%20convict%20to%20attend%20the%20Parliament%20is%20derogatory%20to%20the%20dignity%20of%20the%20Parliament.%20He%20said%2C%20per%20the%20report%2C%20that%20none%20can%20claim%20a%20right%20to%20represent%20an%20electorate.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702572204000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-suspends-conviction-of-bsp-mp-afzal-ansari%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%20clarified%20that%20Ansari%20shall%20not%20be%20disqualified%20to%20contest%20future%20elections%20during%20the%20pendency%20of%20his%20criminal%20appeal%20before%20the%20high%20court.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A4%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsc-suspends-conviction-of-bsp-mp-afzal-ansari%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Chris%20Gayle%20dances%20to%20SRK's%20Lutt%20Putt%20Gaya%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702571856000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105999806%2Cimgsize-49028.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fchris-gayle-steals-the-show-by-dancing-to-shah-rukh-khans-dunki-song-lutt-putt-gaya-heres-what-srk-has-to-say%2Farticleshow%2F105999768.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F105999768.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EShah%20Rukh%20Khan%20responds%20to%20cricketer%20Chris%20Gayle%20dancing%20to%20his%20song%20'Lutt%20Putt%20Gaya'%20from%20th