cts-allegations-of-unlawful-use-of-white-phosphorus-shells-against-lebanon%5C%22%3EIsrael%20has%20rejected%20any%20allegations%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20unlawful%20use%20of%20white%20phosphorus%20in%20Lebanon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20what%20are%20the%20legal%20uses%20of%20this%20chemical%20under%20international%20humanitarian%20law%3F%20And%20can%20its%20use%20be%20considered%20a%20war%20crime%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20white%20phosphorous%20has%20been%20used%20before%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhite%20phosphorous%20is%20a%20chemical%20component%20that%20ignites%20on%20contact%20with%20air%20and%20burns%20at%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Finvestigations%2F2023%2F12%2F11%2Fisrael-us-white-phosphorus-lebanon%2F%5C%22%3E1%2C500%20degree%20Fahrenheit%3C%2Fa%3E%20(815%20Celsius).%20It%20can%20lead%20to%20serious%20injury%20and%20or%20even%20death%20if%20it%20comes%20into%20contact%20with%20humans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHuman%20Rights%20Watch%20regards%20incendiary%20weapons%2C%20such%20as%20white%20phosphorous%20and%20napalm%2C%20as%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2F2023-03-17%2Fexplainer-incendiary-weapons-in-ukraine%2F102093560%5C%22%3Eamong%20the%20cruelest%20weapons%20used%20in%20contemporary%20armed%20conflict%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20due%20to%20their%20impact%20on%20the%20human%20body.%20Says%20one%20Human%20Rights%20Watch%20researcher%3A%20%E2%80%9CIncendiary%20weapons%20are%20weapons%20that%20set%20fire%20or%20burn%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhite%20phosphorus%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jurist.org%2Fcommentary%2F2014%2F12%2Fsascha-dominikbachmann-incendiary-weapons%2F%5C%22%3Ecan%20be%20used%3C%2Fa%3E%20defensively%2C%20though%2C%20as%20a%20smokescreen%20to%20mask%20troop%20movements%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20to%20illuminate%20the%20battlefield%2C%20or%20as%20a%20signalling%20device.%20It%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F12%2Fquestions-and-answers-israels-use-white-phosphorus-gaza-and-lebanon%5C%22%3Ecan%20also%20interfere%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20an%20enemy%E2%80%99s%20infrared%20optics%20and%20weapons%20tracking%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20these%20incendiary%20weapons%20can%20also%20be%20used%20offensively%20in%20mortar%20bombs%2C%20rockets%2C%20and%20artillery%20ammunition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhite%20phosphorous%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2F10%2F13%2Fwhite-phosphorus-chemical-what-is%2F%5C%22%3Ewas%20used%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20many%20adversaries%20in%20both%20the%20First%20and%20Second%20World%20Wars%2C%20targeting%20enemy%20soldiers%20and%20civilians%20alike.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20also%20used%20white%20phosphorus%2C%20alongside%20napalm%2C%20in%20the%20Vietnam%20War%20and%20more%20recently%20in%20Iraq%20during%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2005%2Fnov%2F16%2Firaq.usa%5C%22%3Ebattle%20of%20Fallujah%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202004%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2023%2F10%2F19%2Fwhite-phosphorus-israel-gaza-human-rights-war-crimes-un-icc%2F%5C%22%3Eagainst%20the%20Islamic%20state%20in%20both%20Syria%20and%20Iraq%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20is%20also%20accused%20of%20using%20white%20phosphorus%20indiscriminately%20against%20civilians%20and%20combatants%20in%20both%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abc.net.au%2Fnews%2F2023-03-17%2Fexplainer-incendiary-weapons-in-ukraine%2F102093560%5C%22%3EUkraine%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHuman%20Rights%20Watch%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Freport%2F2009%2F03%2F25%2Frain-fire%2Fisraels-unlawful-use-white-phosphorus-gaza%5C%22%3Ecriticised%3C%2Fa%3E%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20use%20of%20white%20phosphorous%20against%20Hamas%20targets%20in%20Gaza%20in%202008%E2%80%9309%20and%20said%20it%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2009%2F03%2F25%2Fisrael-white-phosphorus-use-evidence-war-crimes%5C%22%3Eevidence%20of%20a%20potential%20war%20crime%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAware%20of%20the%20negative%20publicity%20from%20these%20reports%2C%20the%20Israeli%20Defence%20Forces%20pledged%20in%202013%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Finvestigations%2F2023%2F12%2F11%2Fisrael-us-white-phosphorus-lebanon%2F%5C%22%3Estop%20using%3C%2Fa%3E%20white%20phosphorus%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%20saying%20it%20would%20transition%20to%20gas-based%20smoke%20shells%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20international%20law%20says%20about%20it%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncendiary%20weapons%20fall%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdisarmament.un.org%2Ftreaties%2Ft%2Fccwc%5C%22%3E1980%20Convention%20on%20Certain%20Conventional%20Weapons%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20treaty%20aims%20to%20protect%20civilians%20by%20limiting%20the%20use%20of%20certain%20weapons%20deemed%20particularly%20dangerous.%20A%20protocol%20specifically%20focused%20on%20incendiary%20weapons%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fihl-databases.icrc.org%2Fen%2Fihl-treaties%2Fccw-protocol-iii-1980%2Farticle-1%5C%22%3Edefines%3C%2Fa%3E%20them%20as%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3Eany%20weapon%20or%20munition%20which%20is%20primarily%20designed%20to%20set%20fire%20to%20objects%20or%20to%20cause%20burn%20injury%20to%20persons%20through%20the%20action%20of%20flame%2C%20heat%2C%20or%20combination%20thereof%2C%20produced%20by%20a%20chemical%20reaction%20of%20a%20substance%20delivered%20on%20the%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhite%20phosphorus%20is%20not%20illegal%20under%20international%20law%20and%20the%20law%20of%20armed%20conflict%2C%20as%20long%20as%20it%20is%20being%20used%20defensively%20as%20a%20smokescreen%20or%20as%20battlefield%20illumination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20targeted%20use%20of%20incendiary%20weapons%20directly%20against%20civilians%2C%20however%2C%20is%20illegal%20and%20could%20be%20considered%20a%20war%20crime.%20The%20use%20of%20%E2%80%9Cair-delivered%E2%80%9D%20incendiary%20weapons%20(such%20as%20white%20phosphorus%20dropped%20from%20a%20plane)%20against%20a%20military%20target%20that%20is%20in%20a%20civilian%20area%20is%20also%20prohibited.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20an%20exception%2C%20though%2C%20if%20the%20military%20target%20is%20%E2%80%9Cclearly%20separated%E2%80%9D%20from%20civilians%20and%20all%20%E2%80%9Cfeasible%20precautions%E2%80%9D%20are%20taken%20to%20limit%20incidental%20loss%20of%20civilian%20life%20or%20injuries%20to%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20this%20means%20the%20targeting%20of%20either%20Hamas%20or%20Hezbollah%20is%20permissible%20as%20long%20as%20the%20white%20phosphorus%20is%20not%20air%20delivered%20and%20steps%20are%20taken%20to%20minimise%20the%20harm%20to%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Israel%20is%20accused%20of%20doing%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmnesty%20International%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amnesty.org%2Fen%2Flatest%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2Flebanon-evidence-of-israels-unlawful-use-of-white-phosphorus-in-southern-lebanon-as-cross-border-hostilities-escalate%2F%5C%22%3Ecompiled%20evidence%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20indicates%20white%20phosphorus%20was%20likely%20used%20in%20a%20civilian%20setting%20(the%20Lebanese%20town%20of%20Dheira)%20in%20October.%20Residents%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Finvestigations%2F2023%2F12%2F11%2Fisrael-us-white-phosphorus-lebanon%2F%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Washington%20Post%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20Israeli%20forces%20had%20shelled%20the%20town%20with%20%E2%80%9Cwhite%20phosphorus%20munitions%20for%20hours%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20reports%20need%20a%20thorough%20investigation%20to%20examine%20what%20exactly%20happened%20and%20if%20there%20was%20an%20illegal%20use%20of%20white%20phosphorous%20by%20Israeli%20forces%20or%20whether%20it%20was%20permitted%20under%20the%20guidelines%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20will%20need%20to%20determine%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20if%20white%20phosphorous%20was%20indeed%20used%20and%2C%20if%20it%20was%2C%20whether%20it%20was%20delivered%20via%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F12%2Fquestions-and-answers-israels-use-white-phosphorus-gaza-and-lebanon%5C%22%3Eairburst%20or%20a%20groundburst%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInvestigators%20would%20also%20need%20to%20determine%20if%20the%20forces%20took%20steps%20to%20minimise%20civilian%20harm.%20This%20a%20very%20difficult%20proposition%20in%20the%20current%20conflict%2C%20as%20both%20Hamas%20and%20Hezbollah%20are%20known%20to%20embed%20their%20fighters%20within%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Foct%2F30%2Fhuman-shield-israel-claim-hamas-command-centre-under-hospital-palestinian-civilian-gaza-city%5C%22%3Ecivilian%20population%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAny%20direct%20targeting%20of%20civilians%20or%20indiscriminate%20use%20of%20air-delivered%20incendiary%20weapons%20would%20potentially%20qualify%20as%20a%20war%20crime%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.icrc.org%2Feng%2Fassets%2Ffiles%2Fpublications%2Ficrc-002-0173.pdf%5C%22%3EGeneva%20Conventions%20of%201949%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fog%20of%20war%2C%20it%20is%20more%20important%20than%20ever%20to%20have%20independent%20verification%20of%20the%20actions%20of%20combatants%20on%20both%20sides%20and%20a%20thorough%20investigation%20by%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20(ICC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20prosecution%20of%20any%20alleged%20war%20crimes%20in%20the%20current%20conflict%20remains%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwhy-is-accountability-for-alleged-war-crimes-so-hard-to-achieve-in-the-israel-palestinian-conflict-160864%5C%22%3Eextremely%20difficult%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20is%20due%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20the%20fact%20Israel%20is%20not%20a%20member%20of%20the%20ICC%20and%20rejects%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20jurisdiction%20over%20its%20territory%20and%20both%20Hamas%20and%20Hezbollah%20are%20non-state%20entities.%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F219809%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fsascha-dominik-dov-bachmann-124784%5C%22%3ESascha-Dominik%20(Dov)%20Bachmann%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20in%20Law%20and%20Co-Convener%20National%20Security%20Hub%20(University%20of%20Canberra)%20and%20Research%20Fellow%20(adjunct)%20%E2%80%93%20The%20Security%20Institute%20for%20Governance%20and%20Leadership%20in%20Africa%2C%20Faculty%20of%20Military%20Science%2C%20Stellenbosch%20University-%20NATO%20Fellow%20Asia-Pacific%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-canberra-865%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Canberra%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3Eunder%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fisrael-is-accused-of-using-white-phosphorous-would-this-be-against-international-law-219809%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702540214000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F08114729%2Fimage1170x530cropped-3.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fisrael-hamas-war-what-does-the-international-law-say-on-the-use-of-white-phosphorus%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20the%20ongoing%20war%2C%20Israel%20is%20accused%20of%20using%20the%20chemical%20component%20in%20the%20Le