0the%20Western%20Pacific%20Region%2C%2019%25%20in%20the%20African%20Region%2C%2012%25%20in%20the%20Region%20of%20the%20Americas%2C%2011%25%20in%20the%20Eastern%20Mediterranean%20Region%2C%20and%205%25%20in%20the%20European%20Region%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Froad-deaths-down-by-5-globally-indias-share-rise%2Farticleshow%2F105956424.cms%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20European%20region%20reported%20the%20most%20significant%20drop%20in%20deaths%20since%202010%2C%20at%2036%25%2C%20attributed%20to%20a%20%E2%80%9Csafe%20system%20approach.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Western%20Pacific%20and%20South-East%20Asia%20regions%20reported%20declines%20of%2016%25%20and%202%25%2C%20respectively.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReductions%20in%20deaths%20were%20observed%20in%20108%20countries.%20Notably%2C%20ten%20countries%E2%80%94Belarus%2C%20Brunei%20Darussalam%2C%20Denmark%2C%20Japan%2C%20Lithuania%2C%20Norway%2C%20Russian%20Federation%2C%20Trinidad%20and%20Tobago%2C%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20and%20Venezuela%E2%80%94successfully%20achieved%20the%20target%20reduction%20of%20at%20least%2050%25%20in%20their%20fatality%20numbers.%20However%2C%2066%20countries%2C%20including%2028%20in%20the%20African%20region%2C%20experienced%20a%20rise%20in%20the%20number%20of%20deaths%20since%202010%2C%20the%20WHO%20report%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Froad-deaths-down-by-5-globally-indias-share-rise%2Farticleshow%2F105956424.cms%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702538432000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14114640%2FScreenshot-2023-12-14-at-11.45.46-AM.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fglobal-road-deaths-drop-5-indias-record-worsens-who-report%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India's%20share%20in%20global%20road%20fatalities%20rose%20from%2011%25%20to%2013%25%2C%20with%20number%20of%20deaths%20increasing%20from%201.34%20lakh%20in%202010%20to%201.54%20lakh%20in%202021.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A8%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Furban%2Fglobal-road-deaths-drop-5-indias-record-worsens-who-report%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Feasibility%20Study%20of%20Nepal-China%20Railway%20'on%20Track'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14120229%2Fantoine-beauvillain-0Kw44ElHN3A-unsplash.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20technical%20team%20is%20expected%20to%20complete%20an%20aerial%20survey%20of%20the%20proposed%20Kerung-Kathmandu%20Cross%20Border%20Railway%20within%20this%20month%20as%20the%20fieldwork%20progresses%20smoothly%2C%20a%20senior%20official%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20Railways%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20part%20of%20the%20long-delayed%20detailed%20feasibility%20study%2C%20the%20task%20of%20aerial%20survey%20has%20been%20conducted%20since%20early%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20the%20department.%20The%20Chinese%20technical%20team%20has%20been%20undertaking%20a%20detailed%20feasibility%20study%2C%20which%20is%20supposed%20to%20be%20completed%20within%2042%20months%20of%20its%20start.%20China%20has%20approved%20a%20grant%20assistance%20of%20RMB%20180%20million%20(Rs%203.35%20billion)%20for%20the%20purpose%2C%20according%20to%20the%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSince%20the%20Chinese%20team%20started%20conducting%20an%20aerial%20survey%20using%20drones%20in%20March%20this%20year%2C%20the%20task%20has%20been%20completed%20in%20Nuwakot%20and%20Rasuwa%20districts%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Rohit%20Bisural%2C%20director%20general%20at%20the%20railway%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20process%20of%20obtaining%20necessary%20approval%20for%20the%20survey%20to%20conduct%20the%20aerial%20survey%20in%20Kathmandu%20continues%20and%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20within%20this%20month%20as%20there%20is%20not%20much%20territory%20to%20be%20covered%20by%20the%20proposed%20railway.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Bisural%2C%20work%20on%20a%20detailed%20feasibility%20study%20is%20on%20track.%20%E2%80%9COur%20plan%20was%20to%20complete%20the%20aerial%20survey%20and%20mapping%20within%202023%2C%20which%20is%20expected%20to%20be%20achieved%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeological%20survey%20and%20mapping%2C%20spatial%20technical%20studies%2C%20on-site%20surveying%20and%20mapping%2C%20geological%20survey%2C%20construction%20condition%20studies%2C%20engineering%20studies%2C%20and%20preparation%20of%20the%20feasibility%20study%20report%20are%20other%20tasks%20under%20the%20detailed%20feasibility%20study%2C%20according%20to%20the%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGeological%20survey%20will%20begin%20next%20year%20and%20the%20remaining%20tasks%20are%20expected%20to%20be%20completed%20within%20the%2042-month%20deadline%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Bisural.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20November%2C%20talks%20between%20Nepal%20and%20China%20were%20held%20at%20Xiantao%2C%20China%2C%20to%20review%20the%20progress%20of%20the%20cross-border%20railway%20project.%20%E2%80%9CBoth%20sides%20expressed%20satisfaction%20at%20the%20progress%20in%20the%20feasibility%20study%2C%E2%80%9D%20Bisural%20said.%20Keshav%20Kumar%20Sharma%2C%20secretary%20at%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Physical%20Infrastructure%20and%20Transport%2C%20led%20the%20Nepali%20delegation%20at%20the%20talks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20feasibility%20study%20task%20began%2C%20a%20Chinese%20technical%20team%20representing%20the%20China%20Railway%20First%20Survey%20and%20Design%20Institute%20Group%20visited%20Nepal%20in%20late%20December%20last%20year%20and%20conducted%20a%20reconnaissance%20survey%20of%20the%20railway%20project%2C%20according%20to%20the%20railway%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReconnaissance%20is%20the%20first%20engineering%20survey%20in%20a%20previously%20unsurveyed%20territory%20for%20the%20purpose%20of%20project%20implementation.%20The%20detailed%20feasibility%20study%20began%20only%20in%20March%20this%20year%2C%20the%20department%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20been%20several%20years%20since%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20political%20leaders%20started%20selling%20the%20dream%20of%20cross-border%20railways.%20But%20it%20took%20longer%20than%20expected%20even%20to%20start%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20analysts%20consider%20a%20railway%20connecting%20the%20Chinese%20border%20town%20of%20Kerung%20with%20Kathmandu%20as%20an%20effort%20to%20counter%20India%E2%80%99s%20project%20to%20connect%20the%20Nepali%20capital%20with%20a%20cross-border%20Railway%20via%20Raxaul.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Prime%20Minister%20Pushpa%20Kamal%20Dahal%20visited%20India%20in%20late%20May%20and%20early%20June%2C%20the%20Indian%20side%20had%20handed%20over%20a%20draft%20of%20the%20Final%20Location%20Survey%2C%20of%20the%20proposed%20cross-border%20Raxaul-Kathmandu%20railway%20to%20the%20Nepali%20authorities.%20According%20to%20the%20department%20officials%2C%20the%20Final%20Location%20Survey%20is%20also%20a%20type%20of%20detailed%20feasibility%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20talks%20about%20building%20the%20Kerung-Kathmandu%20railway%20began%20earlier%20than%20the%20Raxaul-Kathmandu%20project%2C%20the%20feasibility%20study%20of%20the%20northern%20connection%20began%20much%20later%20because%20of%20Covid-19%20and%20China%E2%80%99s%20strict%20anti-pandemic%20efforts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChina%20got%20into%20developing%20railways%20in%20Nepal%20when%20former%20prime%20minister%20KP%20Sharma%20Oli%20visited%20Beijing%20in%20March%202016%20during%20his%20first%20stint%20as%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20out%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20trade%20blockade%2C%20Nepal%20sought%20to%20develop%20alternative%20transport%20routes%2C%20citing%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20overdependence%20on%20its%20southern%20neighbour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENepal%20and%20China%20then%20had%20agreed%20that%20the%20two%20sides%20would%20exchange%20ideas%20and%20proposals%20on%20constructing%20cross-border%20railways%20and%20railway%20networks%20in%20Nepal%20and%20support%20enterprises%20to%20start%20related%20preparatory%20work%20as%20soon%20as%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Chinese%20then%20sent%20their%20technical%20teams%20to%20conduct%20a%20preliminary%20feasibility%20study%20for%20the%20proposed%20railway%20in%20November%202017%20and%20May%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20MoU%20was%20signed%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20on%2021%20June%202018%20on%20the%20Cooperation%20in%20Railway%20Project%20when%20Oli%20visited%20China%20during%20his%20second%20stint%20as%20prime%20minister.%20Recalling%20the%20MoU%2C%20the%20two%20sides%20agreed%20to%20conduct%20the%20feasibility%20study%20as%20outlined%20in%20the%20MoU%20when%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fmprc.gov.cn%2Fmfa_eng%2Fwjdt_665385%2F2649_665393%2F201910%2Ft20191013_679597.html%5C%22%3E%C2%A0visited%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Nepal%20in%20October%202019.%20The%20study%20would%20lay%20the%20foundation%20for%20the%20cross-border%20railway.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20feasibility%20study%20could%20not%20move%20ahead%20instantly%20because%20of%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic.%20China%20sent%20its%20technical%20team%20to%20conduct%20a%20reconnaissance%20survey%20in%20December%20last%20year%20and%20another%20team%20early%20this%20year%20for%20the%20feasibility%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20building%20this%20railway%20will%20not%20be%20easy%20from%20both%20technical%20and%20financial%20perspectives%20because%20of%20the%20rough%20terrain%20and%20environmental%20sensitivity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20pre-feasibility%20study%2C%2095%20percent%20of%20the%2073-km%20railway%20network%20will%20need%20tunnelling.%20Its%20construction%20cost%20is%20estimated%20at%20Rs293%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20Bisural.%20There%20are%20also%20concerns%20over%20whether%20the%20project%20is%20financially%20viable%20for%20Nepal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20an%20event%20organised%20on%20Tuesday%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Social%20Inclusion%20and%20Federalism%20(CESIF)%2C%20a%20think%20tank%2C%20on%20Nepal-China%20relations%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Pushpa%20Kamal%20Dahal%E2%80%99s%20recent%20visit%20to%20China%2C%20experts%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fnational%2F2023%2F12%2F13%2Fnepal-should-choose-roads-over-rail-to-china-experts-say%5C%22%3E%C2%A0stressed%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20need%20to%20focus%20more%20on%20road%20connectivity%20than%20railway%2C%20citing%20the%20geographical%20and%20engineering%20challenges%20associated%20with%20railway%20development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20minister%20and%20Nepali%20Congress%20leader%20Minendra%20Rijal%20questioned%20the%20very%20rationale%20of%20bringing%20Chinese%20rail%20to%20Kathmandu.%20%E2%80%9CWhat%20will%20we%20export%20to%20China%20and%20what%20will%20we%20import%20from%20Tibet%20through%20the%20railroad%3F%20So%20let%E2%80%99s%20build%20roads%20instead.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrithvi%20Man%20Shrestha%20is%20a%20political%20reporter%20for%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Kathmandu%20Post%3Cem%3E%2C%20covering%20the%20governance-related%20issues%20including%20corruption%20and%20irregularities%20in%20the%20government%20machinery.%20Before%20joining%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Kathmandu%20Post%3Cem%3E%20in%202009%2C%20he%20worked%20at%20nepalnews.com%20and%20%3C%2Fem%3ERising%20Nepal%3Cem%3E%20primarily%20covering%20the%20issues%20of%20political%20and%20economic%20affairs%20for%20three%20years.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkathmandupost.com%2Fnational%2F2023%2F12%2F14%2Ffeasibility-study-of-nepal-china-railway-on-track-department-says%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%3C%2Fem%3E%20The%20Kathmandu%20Post.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702536640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14120229%2Fantoine-beauvillain-0Kw44ElHN3A-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Ffeasibility-study-of-nepal-china-railway-on-track%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Many%20analysts%20consider%20a%20railway%20connecting%20the%20Chinese%20border%20town%20of%20Kerung%20with%20Kathmandu%20as%20an%20effort%20to%20counter%20India%E2%80%99s%20project%20to%20connect%20the%20Nepali%20capital%20with%20a%20cross-border%20Railway%20via%20Raxaul.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Ffeasibility-study-of-nepal-china-railway-on-track%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Last%20Pillar%20of%20Indian%20Democracy%20Has%20Fallen%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13130248%2FSupreme-Court-p.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20has%20given%20a%20succession%20of%20judgements%20that%20have%20eroded%20civil%20society%E2%80%99s%C2%A0%20faith%20in%20its%20readiness%20to%20uphold%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20and%20protect%20its%20secular%2C%20ethno-federal%20democracy%20from%20the%20relentless%20attack%20that%20has%20been%20launched%20upon%20it%20by%20the%20government%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20his%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah.%20But%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmodi-zakia-jafri-command-responsibility%5C%22%3Emost%20perverse%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20previous%20decisions%20pales%20into%20insignificance%20before%20that%20of%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-kashmir-article-370-verdict%5C%22%3Ejudgment%20upholding%20the%20reading%20down%20of%20Article%20370%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Constitution%20on%205%2C%20August%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%2C%20and%20most%20disturbing%2C%20editorials%20that%20I%20have%20read%20in%20six%20decades%20as%20a%20journalist%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Fominously-anti-federal-on-the-supreme-courts-judgement-on-article-370-and-jks-special-status%2Farticle67628150.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20described%20how%2C%20by%20upholding%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20opened%20the%20way%20for%20his%20or%20any%20future%20government%20to%20amend%20the%20Constitution%20without%20having%20to%20bother%20with%20getting%20a%20two-thirds%20majority%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20Parliament.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20is%20simple%3A%20take%20advantage%20of%2C%20or%20create%2C%20a%20law%20and%20order%20situation%20in%20a%20state%2C%20declare%20President%E2%80%99s%20Rule%20under%20Article%20356%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20claim%20that%20the%20president%20(or%20governor)%20now%20has%20all%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20state%20legislature%2C%C2%A0%20and%20enact%20whatever%20change%20the%20state%20government%20did%20not%20want%20to%20make.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20way%20in%20which%20the%20Modi%20government%20will%20use%20this%20interpretation%20of%20the%20Constitution%20needs%20no%20imagination.%20In%20three%20states%20the%20BJP-appointed%20governors%20have%20refused%20to%20give%20their%20assent%20to%20Bills%20or%20laws%20passed%20by%20the%20legislature.%20In%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20in%20a%20direct%20violation%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20the%20governor%20has%20refused%20to%20give%20it%20even%20after%20the%20Bill%20has%20been%20returned%20to%20him%20a%20second%20time.%20This%20was%20an%20express%20violation%20of%20the%20Constitution%2C%20but%20one%20that%20was%20directly%20instigated%20by%20the%20Union%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20sent%20a%20team%20of%2040%20CBI%20officials%20to%20Kolkata%2C%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcbis-attempted-arrest-of-kolkata-police-commissioner-was-an-attack-on-federalism%5C%22%3Earrest%20a%20serving%20police%20commissioner%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20state%20government%20and%20bring%20him%20to%20Delhi%20for%20interrogation.%20Its%20attempt%20was%20foiled%20only%20because%20there%20was%20an%20elected%C2%A0%20state%20government%20whose%20police%20rose%20in%20defence%20of%20their%20commissioner%20and%20%E2%80%98arrested%E2%80%99%20the%20CBI%20officials%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22What%20Will%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20Article%20370%20Judgment%20Mean%20for%20Politics%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%3F%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-will-the-supreme-courts-article-370-judgment-mean-for-politics-in-jk%5C%22%3EWhat%20Will%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20Article%20370%20Judgment%20Mean%20for%20Politics%20in%20J%26amp%3BK%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Delhi%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20taken%20advantage%20of%20its%20already%20being%20a%20union%20territory%20to%20arrest%20no%20less%20august%20a%20personage%20than%20its%20elected%20deputy%20chief%20minister%2C%20Manish%20Sisodia%2C%20and%20has%20been%20holding%20him%20without%20bail%20and%20despite%20being%20unable%20to%20frame%20a%20charge%20against%20him%20for%20ten%20months.%20Not%20Satisfied%20with%20that%2C%20Modi%20is%20now%20attempting%20to%20do%20the%20same%20with%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20Arvind%20Kejriwal%2C%20himself.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20are%20the%20actions%20of%20a%20tyrant%2C%20not%20of%20the%20elected%20leader%20of%20a%20democratic%20government%2C%20and%20all%20have%20been%20taken%C2%A0%20before%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20and%20his%20colleagues%E2%80%99%20eyes.%20How%20long%20do%20they%20think%20it%20will%20be%20before%20Modi%20begins%20to%20use%20the%20freedom%20their%20verdict%20has%20given%20him%2C%20to%20start%20overturning%20opposition%20governments%20in%20order%20to%20bend%20the%20whole%20of%20India%20to%20his%20and%20his%20Hindutva%20colleagues%E2%80%99%20will%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20justify%20its%20decision%2C%20the%20bench%20has%20put%20forward%20two%20other%20supporting%20arguments.%20The%20first%20is%20that%20Article%20370%20was%20placed%20in%20part%2021%20of%20the%20Constitution%20titled%20%E2%80%9CTemporary%2C%20Transitional%20and%20Special%20Provisions%E2%80%9D.%20Thus%20it%20was%20never%20meant%20to%20be%20permanent.%20So%20all%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20has%20done%20is%20to%20close%20the%20chapter%20on%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20is%20that%20over%20the%20decades%20since%20the%20accession%2C%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20laws%20have%20in%20any%20case%20been%20brought%20in%20line%20progressively%20with%20those%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20India.%20So%20as%20the%20government%20has%20argued%2C%20the%20autonomy%20shielded%20by%20Article%20370%20had%20been%20been%20%E2%80%98gradually%20eroded%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20so%20deliberate%20a%20misreading%20of%20the%20Constitution%20that%20it%20leaves%20one%20gasping%20for%20breath.%20How%20could%20the%20learned%20judges%20not%20know%20that%20%E2%80%98temporary%E2%80%99%20had%20to%20be%20read%20within%20its%20temporal%20and%20political%20context%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constitution%20was%20drafted%20in%201948-49%20and%20adopted%20by%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20on%20November%2026%2C%201949.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20India%20was%20still%20a%20dominion%20of%20the%20British%20Commonwealth.%20The%20princely%20state%20of%20Kashmir%20had%20acceded%20to%20India%20but%20two-fifths%20of%20it%20was%20occupied%20by%20Pakistan%20and%20war%20was%20still%20raging%20there.%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20accession%20to%20India%20had%20been%20confirmed%20by%20the%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%2C%20subject%20to%20a%20plebiscite.%20But%20Pakistan%20had%20refused%20to%20vacate%20occupied%20Kashmir%2C%20because%20it%20knew%2C%20as%20British%20high%20commissioner%20to%20Pakistan%20Sir%20Patrick%20Graftey-Smith%20had%20reported%20to%20London%20from%20Karachi%20as%20early%20as%20October%201947%20when%20the%20invasion%20of%20Kashmir%20had%20just%20begun%2C%20that%20it%20would%20lose%20it%20if%20one%20were%20to%20be%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Governors'%20Pocket%20Veto%20Compromises%20Constitutional%20Probity%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fgovernors-pocket-veto-compromises-constitutional-probity%5C%22%3EGovernors%E2%80%99%20Pocket%20Veto%20Compromises%20Constitutional%20Probity%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Constituent%20Assembly%20knew%20that%20substantial%20amendments%20would%20be%20needed%20when%20the%20two%20parts%20of%20Kashmir%20were%20reunited.%20Thus%20%3Cem%3Eit%20was%20the%20boundaries%20of%20Kashmir%20that%20were%20temporary%20when%20the%20Constitution%20was%20adopted.%20%3C%2Fem%3ESince%20%E2%80%98Azad%E2%80%99%20Kashmir%20is%20now%20generally%20accepted%20as%20a%20province%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20the%20ceasefire%20line%20has%20become%20the%20de-facto%20boundary%20between%20India%20and%20Pakistan%20in%20Kashmir%2C%20the%20word%20temporary%20has%20lost%20its%20meaning.%20It%20was%20the%20worst%20kind%20of%20sleight%20of%20hand%20for%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20have%20given%20this%20term%20a%20wholly%20different%20meaning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%E2%80%99s%20other%20justification%20for%20its%20verdict%20is%20equally%20flawed.%20It%20is%20true%20that%20over%20the%20past%20seven%20decades%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20laws%20and%20constitutional%20safeguards%20have%20been%20brought%20more%20and%20more%20in%20line%20with%20those%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20India.%20The%20Instrument%20of%20Accession%20had%20brought%20only%20defence%2C%20foreign%20policy%20and%20communications%20within%20the%20ambit%20of%20Central%20power.%20It%20was%20the%20Delhi%20Agreement%20of%201952%2C%20overseen%20by%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%2C%20that%20began%20the%20integration%20of%20government%20in%20all%20spheres%20between%20the%20state%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJust%20how%20comprehensive%20it%20was%20can%20be%20judged%20from%20the%20range%20of%20subjects%20covered%3A%20These%20included%20the%20appointment%20of%20the%20head%20of%20the%20state%3B%20the%20extension%20of%20all%20the%20civic%20and%20fundamental%20rights%20of%20citizens%20of%20India%20to%20persons%20domiciled%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%3B%20and%20extension%20of%20the%20jurisdiction%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20integrated%20the%20fiscal%20system%20of%20the%20state%20with%20that%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20India%2C%20thereby%20giving%20Kashmiris%20full%20and%20free%20access%20to%20the%20vast%20Indian%20market.%20Finally%20it%20extended%20key%20symbols%20of%20statehood%20like%20the%20national%20flag%2C%20and%20the%20emergency%20powers%20of%20the%20Indian%20state%20to%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20agreement%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20Kashmir%E2%80%99s%20integration%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20India.%20A%20decade%20later%2C%20in%201963%2C%20Nehru%20said%20that%20Article%20370%20has%20been%20eroded%20and%20the%20process%20of%20gradual%20erosion%20was%20going%20on.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20home%20minister%20Gulzari%20Lal%20Nanda%2C%20described%20article%20370%20as%20a%20tunnel%20to%20take%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20to%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20released%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%20from%20incarceration%20and%20allowed%20him%20to%20resume%20his%20chief%20ministership%20of%20Kashmir%2C%2023%20constitutional%20orders%20had%20been%20promulgated%20to%20further%20integrate%20the%20state%20into%20the%20Indian%20Union%2C%20and%20262%20Union%20laws%20had%20been%20applied%20to%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20chosen%20to%20ignore%20is%20that%20all%20this%20was%20done%20with%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20Kashmir%20governments%20of%20the%20time.%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%20had%20signed%20the%20Delhi%20agreement%20only%20after%20convening%20a%20constituent%20Assembly%20with%2075%20members%2C%20to%20approve%20of%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20decades%20that%20followed%2C%20more%20and%20more%20all-India%20laws%20and%20provisions%20were%20extended%20to%20Kashmir%20as%20well%20with%20the%20full%20consent%2C%20often%20at%20the%20request%20of%2C%20the%20Kashmir%20government.%20As%20Sheikh%20Abdullah%E2%80%99s%20talks%20with%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20special%20representative%2C%20G.%20Parthasarathy%2C%20before%20returning%C2%A0%20to%20power%20showed%2C%20there%20was%20next%20to%20nothing%20left%20that%20he%20wanted%20to%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20process%20was%20a%20world%20away%20from%20the%20sleight%20of%20hand%20that%20the%20Modi%20government%20used%20in%202019%2C%20to%20%E2%80%98complete%E2%80%99%20the%20integration.%20The%20contrast%20between%20%E2%80%98erosion%20by%20consent%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98erosion%20through%20brute%20force%E2%80%99%20was%20vividly%20demonstrated%20by%20the%20weeks-long%20curfews%2C%20the%20complete%20shut%20down%20of%20internet%20services%2C%20and%20the%20paralysis%20of%20transport%20even%20afterwards%20that%20forced%20people%20catching%20flights%20out%20of%20Kashmir%20to%20walk%20kilometres%20to%20get%20to%20the%20airport.%20For%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20to%20have%20glossed%20over%20this%20stark%20and%20humiliating%20difference%20is%20inexcusable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20after%20two%20foreign%20governments%20have%20accused%20the%20Modi%20government%20of%20carrying%20out%20or%20planning%20extra-judicial%20killings%20on%20their%20soil%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20sole%20remaining%20pillar%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20once%20vaunted%2C%20and%20much%20envied%2C%20democracy%20has%20finally%20fallen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPrem%20Shankar%20Jha%20is%20a%20veteran%20journalist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20name%3D%5C%22_ftn1%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-last-pillar-of-indian-democracy-has-fallen%23_ftnref1%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702534737000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F13130248%2FSupreme-Court-p.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-last-pillar-of-indian-democracy-has-fallen%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22By%20upholding%20the%20Article%20370%20decision%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20opened%20the%20way%20for%20the%20government%20to%20amend%20the%20Constitution%20without%20having%20to%20bother%20with%20getting%20a%20two-thirds%20majority%20in%20both%20houses%20of%20Parliament.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A83%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fthe-last-pillar-of-indian-democracy-has-fallen%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22MP%3A%20Newly%20Sworn-in%20CM%20Places%20Curbs%20on%20Loudspeakers%20at%20Religious%20Places%2C%20Sale%20of%20Meat%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F14110618%2FEffect-29.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20newly%C2%A0sworn-in%20chief%20minister%20of%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Mohan%20Yadav%2C%20has%20placed%20curbs%20on%20the%20use%20of%20loudspeakers%20at%20religious%20places%20and%20the%20sale%20of%20meat%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYadav%20was%20administered%20the%20oath%20of%20office%20by%20governor%20Mangubhai%20C.%20Patel%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20a%20galaxy%20of%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20leaders%2C%20including%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20December%2013%2C%20Bhopal.%20With%20Yadav%20taking%20over%20the%20reins%20of%20the%20state%20government%2C%20it%20marked%20the%20end%20of%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%E2%80%99s%2018-year%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWithin%20hours%20of%20assuming%20charge%2C%20Yadav%20presided%20over%20his%20first%20Cabinet%20meeting%2C%20following%20which%20he%20issued%20directions%20to%20the%20effect%20that%20loudspeakers%2FDJs%2C%20etc.%2C%20can%20be%20used%20only%20as%20per%20the%20prescribed%20norms%20at%20any%20type%20of%20religious%20place%20or%20in%20public%20places.%20Known%20for%20his%20communal%20rhetoric%20and%20aggressive%20Hindutva%2C%20Yadav%2C%20as%20the%20head%20of%20the%20government%2C%20issued%20directives%20to%20%E2%80%9Cban%20illegal%20buying%20and%20selling%20of%20meat%2C%20fish%2C%20etc.%2C%20in%20the%20open%20without%20licence%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20an%20%E2%80%9Cintensive%20campaign%20will%20be%20launched%E2%80%9D%20to%20this%20effect%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fnew-cm-mohan-yadav-first-order-prohibits-loudspeakers-religious-places-permissible-limits-9067201%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Cabinet%20meeting%20was%20attended%20by%20Jagdish%20Devda%20and%20Rajendra%20Shukla%2C%20who%20were%20sworn%20in%20alongside%20Yadav%20as%20his%20deputies.%20Other%20ministers%20of%20the%20state%20cabinet%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20announced%20and%20sworn%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20issue%20of%20loudspeakers%2C%20the%20Cabinet%20decided%20to%20form%20flying%20squads%20across%20all%20districts%20to%20check%20noise%20pollution%20and%20the%20illegal%20use%20of%20loudspeakers.%20These%20squads%20will%20regularly%20and%20randomly%20inspect%20religious%20and%20public%20places%20where%20loudspeakers%20are%20used.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20violation%2C%20authorities%20have%20been%20ordered%20to%20investigate%20the%20matter%20within%20a%20maximum%20of%20three%20days%20and%20submit%20the%20report%20to%20the%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Cabinet%20also%20decided%20to%20come%20up%20with%20%E2%80%9Cfood%20safety%20rules%E2%80%9D%20to%20ensure%20meat%20shops%20and%20shops%20selling%20eggs%20adhere%20to%20guidelines%2C%20by%20creating%20awareness%20among%20the%20public%20as%20well%20as%20shop%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECalling%20the%20upcoming%20consecration%20of%20the%20Ram%20Temple%20in%20Ayodhya%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20fortune%E2%80%9D%2C%20Yadav%20told%20the%20media%2C%20after%20the%20Cabinet%20meeting%2C%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgovernment%20will%20welcome%20all%20the%20Ram%20devotees%20in%20every%20district%2C%20who%20are%20en%20route%20to%20the%20Ram%20mandir%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmohan-yadav-little-known-outside-ujjan-bjps-cm-pick-for-mp-baffles-party-leaders-cadres%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%2C%20the%20choice%20of%20Yadav%20as%20chief%20minister%20baffled%20both%20party%20leaders%20and%20cadres.%20The%20BJP%20decided%20to%20go%20with%20Yadav%20(54)%2C%20who%20is%20relatively%20unknown%20outside%20of%20Ujjain.%20The%20party%20high%20command%20sprang%20a%20surprise%20by%20ignoring%20half%20a%20dozen%20other%20claimants%20for%20the%20post%2C%20much%20senior%20to%20Yadav%2C%20including%20Kailash%20Vijayvargiya%2C%20Narendra%20Singh%20Tomar%2C%20and%20Prahlad%20Singh%20Patel.%20Except%20for%20former%20chief%20minister%20Shivraj%20Singh%20Chouhan%2C%20none%20said%20to%20have%20had%20prior%20information%20about%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20anointment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidered%20a%20committed%20footsoldier%20of%20the%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%2C%20Yadav%20has%C2%A0thrived%20financially%20and%20politically%20by%20mouthing%20provocative%20language%20against%20Muslims